pages.content: Hello I am Tashi. I am a Tibetan boy. I am 9 years old.
I live on a mountain with my family. I want to introduce Tibetan daily life.
My family consists of my grandfather, my parents and my brother and me.
I wake up in the morning and go to the river to wash my face. My dog always chases me.
In summer time, there are lots of flowers near the river.
My brother and I like apples. We eat apples in the morning.
My mom makes milk tea everyday.
My mom waters and feeds the sheep and the yaks.
Today my father bridles the horse and rides.
We went to the restaurant in town and we ate food including mushrooms. We drank tea in a tea shop.
I like vegetable momo. My brother likes mutton.
When we came back, we met some Buddhist pilgrims. They made offering of lotus and orange in the temple.
I saw a fox chasing a cat near my family's tent.
In the evening, we read from a book with my grandfather. He wears glasses; he shows us a map of the world.
We live near the Tibetan Himalayas with our friends. You are welcome anytime.
